# DATABASE_URL — Postgres connection. The db client and verify-schema.mjs
# auto-select the driver by this URL (IMP-259):
#   * LOCAL DEV / CI: a standard Postgres URL uses node-postgres (`pg`), so
#     `pnpm drizzle-kit push` applies the schema to a local database.
#         DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/app
#   * PROD (Vercel/Neon): a *.neon.tech / vercel URL uses neon-http (wss).
#         DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST.neon.tech/DB?sslmode=require
#   Override the heuristic with DB_DRIVER=pg|neon if your host is atypical.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/app
# Vercel injects CRON_SECRET for authenticated cron invocations.
CRON_SECRET=
# Base URL the in-app API client (src/lib/api/client.ts) calls. For a
# single serverless Next.js app this is the app's own origin.
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
